choices.text:
ennui. The monotonous work, the claustrophobic home (gay), to my quiet demeanor and doing what I consider Inconsequential.

Today I spent pretty much the entire day lying half-clothed (not bragging, just writing a diary and point out the level of ennui), in my bed, in my room, in my tiny house just thinking. Not infinite, not eternal introspection... just sitting and thinking about things, playing the same notes, the same songs in my mind over, and over again until I could not even recall, in that moment, what the song was I thinking about, what holes did I intend to fill, what grips had I wanted to tuck in and weave… In all honesty, at one point I was having a beer while watching a show, but I wasn’t really having a beer… I just imagined the taste of the cold beer and was enervated… a mixture of shelved guilt and guilt-less joy at being a perigot…

…My God do I love Perigot… he is a good soul, he is slow, he is sexy, he is pensive… he is creative, he is prancing in clown shoes, and yet he has suffered so… pain, anxiety, depression, futility… no one has more pain than me, I welcome pain like a friend… nonetheless I have spaces in me, many uncharted and never filled spaces… they are all Perigot has gotten
